{"lessons": [{"title": "basics", "theory": "<p>there are 21 letters in [LANGNAME]. since this is your own language, you can choose any pronunciation you like but this is suggested one:</p>\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>{a}</td>\n<td><strong>a</strong>rm</td>\n<td>{j}</td>\n<td><strong>y</strong>es</td>\n<td>{r}</td>\n<td><strong>r</strong>ed</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>{b}</td>\n<td><strong>b</strong>ed&nbsp;</td>\n<td>{k}</td>\n<td><strong>c</strong>at</td>\n<td>{s}</td>\n<td><strong>s</strong>un&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>{d}</td>\n<td><strong>d</strong>ad</td>\n<td>{l}</td>\n<td><strong>l</strong>ake</td>\n<td>{$}</td>\n<td><strong>sh</strong>e&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>{e}</td>\n<td>c<strong>a</strong>t</td>\n<td>{m}</td>\n<td><strong>m</strong>ap</td>\n<td>{t}</td>\n<td><strong>t</strong>ime&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>{f}</td>\n<td><strong>f</strong>eel</td>\n<td>{n}</td>\n<td><strong>n</strong>ose</td>\n<td>{u}</td>\n<td>p<strong>u</strong>t&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>{g}</td>\n<td><strong>g</strong>et</td>\n<td>{o}</td>\n<td>c<strong>a</strong>ll&nbsp;</td>\n<td>{v}</td>\n<td><strong>v</strong>oice&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>{i}</td>\n<td>h<strong>i</strong>t&nbsp;</td>\n<td>{p}</td>\n<td>ma<strong>p</strong>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>{z}</td>\n<td><strong>z</strong>oo&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>declarative sentences have SVO order i.e. subject-verb-object, like in english</p>\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5px\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td>english</td>\n<td>[LANGNAME]</td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>i see a cat</td>\n<td>[i see cat]</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>as you can see, there are no articles in [LANGNAME]</p>\n<p>personal pronouns have similar forms in nominative and accusative cases</p>\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5px\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td>english nom.</td>\n<td>english acc.</td>\n<td>[LANGNAME]</td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>i</td>\n<td>me</td>\n<td>[i]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>we</td>\n<td>us</td>\n<td>[we]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>you <em>(sing.)</em></td>\n<td>you</td>\n<td>[you]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>you <em>(pl.)</em></td>\n<td>you</td>\n<td>[youp]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>he</td>\n<td>him</td>\n<td>[he]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>she</td>\n<td>her</td>\n<td>[she]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>it</td>\n<td>it</td>\n<td>[it]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>they</td>\n<td>them</td>\n<td>[they]</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>", "exercises": [{"eng": "i eat an apple", "gen": "i eat apple"}, {"eng": "you see an apple", "gen": "you see apple"}, {"eng": "i don't see the dog", "gen": "i nosee dog"}, {"eng": "i am from england", "gen": "i be from {england}"}, {"eng": "they love dogs", "gen": "they love doges"}, {"eng": "he loves apples", "gen": "he love apples"}], "words": ["i", "(to) eat", "apple", "you", "(to) see", "dog", "(to) be", "from", "{england}", "they", "he", "(to) love"]}]}